.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-ROUTESTOPPED 5 "2026-04-24" "shorewall-nft 1.10.2" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-routestopped \- legacy stopped-state access list for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I routestopped
file is the legacy mechanism for keeping specific (interface, host) pairs
reachable when the firewall is in the stopped state (after
.BR "shorewall\-nft stop" ).

For new configurations prefer
.IR shorewall\-nft\-stoppedrules (5),
which supports the full rule grammar.
.I routestopped
is retained for backward compatibility.

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/routestopped
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
INTERFACE	yes	Interface name
HOSTS	yes	Host IP or CIDR reachable via this interface
OPTIONS	no	notrack, routeback
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Keep the management interface reachable while stopped:
.RS
.nf
#INTERFACE  HOSTS
eth1        10.0.99.0/24
.fi
.RE
.PP
Keep SSH access from a specific host:
.RS
.nf
eth0        10.0.1.5     -  tcp  22
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-stoppedrules (5)

